Code of Conduct
Purpose
To create a welcoming and respectful environment for all participants, this project is committed to being an inclusive and harassment-free space for everyone, regardless of age, gender, background, or identity.
This Code of Conduct applies to all project-related spaces, both online and offline.

Summary
Treat others with respect and kindness.
Be open to constructive feedback and give it respectfully.
Focus on what's best for the project and community.
Avoid unacceptable behaviors.
Report any issues to project leaders.

Guidelines
Be Respectful and Inclusive
Use kind and respectful language.
Refer to people using their correct names and pronouns.
Avoid offensive or exclusionary language.
Respect differences and be welcoming to everyone.
Be open to new ideas and viewpoints.
Help ensure that everyone feels included, regardless of their background.
Give and Accept Constructive Feedback
Keep feedback helpful and respectful.
When receiving feedback, remember it is part of the learning process. If it feels unfair or harsh, speak to a project leader.
Focus on the Community
Listen actively to others and ensure everyone has a chance to contribute.
Be mindful of how your words and actions affect others.
Learn from mistakes and support each other.

Unacceptable Behaviors
The following actions are not acceptable:
Using offensive or inappropriate language.
Trolling, insults, or personal attacks.
Sharing private information without consent.
Any behavior that would make the project space uncomfortable for others.

Reporting Issues
If you see or experience behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it to the project leaders. All reports will be handled discreetly and respectfully.

Responsibilities of Project Leaders
Project leaders are responsible for ensuring that the project remains a respectful and welcoming space. They may remove or edit any contributions that do not align with this Code of Conduct.

This Code of Conduct is adapted from various open-source guidelines to suit the needs of this project. Especially from RCOS COMMUNITY CODE OF CONDUCT
